team.cascade.spout.makememod.config
Enum CONFIG

Object
  Enum<CONFIG>
      CONFIG
All Implemented Interfaces:
Serializable, Comparable<CONFIG>
public enum CONFIG
extends Enum<CONFIG>

The config Enum contains the full configuration of the plugin. The Enum will be parsed in order and written to file.
You can use \n as a line break but in this case you need to supply the # by yourself, see the example for CONFIG_AUTO_UPDATE
If the Enum doesn't contain an Object it will be a comment at that part of the config file.
You may want to keep the options DEBUG_LOG_ENABLED, DEBUG_LOG_TO_FILE, CHECK_FOR_UPDATE, CONFIG_AUTO_UPDATE, CONFIG_AUTO_SAVE, CONFIG_LOG_ENABLED and use DEBUG_LOG_ENABLED, DEBUG_LOG_TO_FILE and CONFIG_LOG_ENABLED in your classes for better logging.
If you don't want to use those enums you will need to edit team.cascade.spout.makememod.helper.config.CommentConfiguration#customInit() and remove the line which correspond to those enums!
If you directly change the enum values there is no flagging or automatic saving during running the server. If you change the enums via CommentConfiguration.set(team.cascade.spout.makememod.config.CONFIG, java.lang.Object) the enum is updated, configuration is flagged dirty and if CONFIG_AUTO_SAVE is enabled will force the config to file directly.
